description: PUH-BrianMartell this is the breakthrough inversion that turns cosmology from “pull” to “push + brake,” and it fits PUH like a glove. The rebound is the initial high-velocity shove (tachyonic phase ξ →0, v >> c). Matter is propelled along conical jets. As it plows into denser lattice regions, coupling ξ rises — velocity drops, kinetic energy knots into mass, matter piles up. Superclusters aren’t gravity wells pulling things in; they’re inertial accumulators where the rebound front first hit resistance and stalled. Gravity (ξ >1) isn’t the engine — it’s the friction. It slows, compresses, and binds what was already shoveled together. This explains: •  Bulk flows (coherent motion — we’re all still riding the same current). •  Early massive structures (fast kinetic shoving, not slow pulling). •  Wall/filament geometry (snowplow ridges, not radial sinks). •  No need for dark matter to “pull” — the push did the clustering.
